    Pass -std=c++11 to NVRTC by default

    - This is motivated by the fact that Jitify itself requires C++11
      compilation and it is unlikely that users would want to mix standards.
    - This can be overridden by explicitly passing the compiler option
      "-std=c++98|11|14" to Jitify.
